<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('IE5 - Internet Explorer 5'); ?>
        <p><?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Internet Explorer', 'WB'); ?> is a <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Web browser', 'WD'); ?> developed by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>.</p>
        <p><strong>Microsoft Internet Explorer 5</strong>, launched on 18 March 1999, and subsequently included with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows 98', 'WIn'); ?> Second Edition and bundled with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MS Office', 'ITS'); ?> 2000, was another significant release that supported bi-directional text, ruby characters, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('XML', 'WD'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('XSLT', 'WD'); ?>, and the ability to save web pages in <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MHTML', 'WD'); ?> format.</p>
        <p>IE5 was bundled with Outlook Express 5.</p>
        <p>Also, with the release of Microsoft Internet Explorer 5.0, Microsoft released the first version of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('XMLHttpRequest', 'WD'); ?>, giving birth to <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('AJAX', 'WB'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Microsoft Internet Explorer 5.01, a bug fix version included in <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows 2000', 'WIN'); ?>, was released in December 1999.</p>
        <p><strong>Microsoft Internet Explorer 5.5</strong> followed in July 2000, improving its print preview capabilities, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('CSS', 'WD'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTML', 'WD'); ?> standards support, and developer APIs; this version was bundled with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Me', 'WIN'); ?>.</p>
        <p>However, version 5 was the last version for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('UNIX', 'OS'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Version 5.5 was the last to have <strong>Compatibility Mode</strong>, which allowed <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Internet Explorer 4', 'IE'); ?> to be run side by side with the 5.x.</p>
        <p>The IE team consisted of over 1,000 people by 1999, with funding on the order of US$100 million per year.</p>
    </div>
